Today, Montaque introduced a new network geared towards providing key support to creators who are positioned to take the next step in their creative Through Crater, the founder says they will have opportunities to build professional relationships with fellow creators, launch their ânext waveâ ideas and secure the kind of funding that will help them maintain sustainable Additionally, the network will partner with Group Black to amplify the works of its âCrater is a creator network where the next wave of culture is made and monetized,â Montaque explained to âWeâre really trying to change the economic situation of these creators and drive opportunity for  Montaque is joined Sarah Aitken, who will serve as According to Aitken, the network is mainly galvanized to provide access âpast the wallâ that largely keeps creators from securing success beyond a basisâespecially when it comes to marginalized creatives , who routinely experience substantial gaps in pay and âThereâs culture to be unlocked beyond that wall and thereâs value in that culture for brands, media, consumers and everybody else around the edges,â said âAnd obviously, we want to create a massive amount of value for the creators in that  Creator, meet village Upon its launch, Crater boasts of an inaugural group of popular creators who have signed on as official members, including understand the responsibility that comes with this opportunity, and I look forward to using Crater to continue to advance opportunities for those that come after me through my  GROUP BLACK CEO TRAVIS MONTAQUE HELPS BRANDS INVEST IN A MORE INCLUSIVE FUTURE Added Grace Africa, âAs a multifaceted creator myself, Iâm so happy to work with Crater on my upcoming comedy Crater sees creators like myself as more than just social media personalities, they see us as entrepreneurs and give us access to funding and opportunities that were never presented  In addition to creators, Crater sees early support from major industry figures like Jermaine Dupri, marketing veteran Bozoma Saint John, Shar Caesar Douglas, and creator entrepreneurs Julie Ann Crommett, Keith Dorsey and Christen Nino De Guzmanâall of whom make up the networkâs advisory âI chose to align myself with Crater because I strongly believe in the vision and I know that the market for creators to monetize their own creativity will only continue to grow, â said Dupri, who will serve as head advisory board âFor too long diverse creators have not been compensated or celebrated for their impact on Crater exists to change that, and I look forward to being a part of that  As Crater continues to expand its reach, Montaque and Aitken encourage interested creators to sign up on the networkâs website to learn A new approach to understanding and combating disease Teal is developing advanced analytics capabilities to better understand aging and Their platform has been developed through years of research by the lab at Stanford University and is built on previous discoveries that proteins found in the blood can be used to develop markers of age and physiology that reveal functional insights and predict disease The science Teal is pioneering focuses on developing a deeper understanding of aging biology using novel proteomics These new learnings serve as powerful predictors of health Teal uniquely approaches the challenge of measuring biological age by developing aging models using proteins, and not Their technology has been demonstrated to be powerful at measuring the current physiological state of organs as well as predicting future degeneration and disease Our Science Teal’s technology builds on over years of academic research conducted in Stanford University s The lab has focused is on brain aging and neurodegeneration with a specific interest in cognitive decline and Alzheimer’s From this work, it was discovered that circulatory blood factors can modulate brain structure and function and factors from young organisms can rejuvenate old Teal s science was built on the belief that a better understanding of aging biology will ultimately lead to insights that will accelerate the identification of new approaches for treating aging and disease and their work focuses on the use of human proteomics as a tool for understanding aging and measuring Our Team Tony , PhD Alex Boches Markus Okumus Investor Jarod Rutledge Hamilton Oh A New Frontier in Measuring Aging Subscribe to our newsletter to receive news and Enter your email here Sign Up Thanks for submitting! Acupuncture | Luna Veterinary Care Team Pricing Services Pet Euthanasia Acupuncture Pet Cremation Pet Hospice Care Resources FAQ How Will I Know It s Time How to Grieve the Loss of Your Pet Quality of Life Assessment Contact Find a Vet Acupuncture Like in people, acupuncture for pets relieves symptoms like pain and It’s a common treatment in traditional Chinese medicine that’s been used for thousands of And it can help cats and dogs feel better Our certified veterinary acupuncturists provide gentle, treatments to give your pet the best quality of What is pet acupuncture? Acupuncture for dogs and cats is based on the principles of traditional Chinese veterinary medicine (TCVM), which focuses on correcting imbalances of Before an acupuncture session, our veterinary acupuncturists will examine your pet and develop a treatment During an acupuncture session, the veterinarian inserts thin, sterile needles into specific points along your pet’s This redirects energy and stimulates What does acupuncture for dogs and cats treat? Acupuncture treats a number of conditions by stimulating the body’s healing It improves blood circulation and promotes the release of hormones that act as natural painkillers and stress Pet acupuncture is commonly used alongside standard veterinary care and provides additional treatment options for conditions including: disorders and metabolic diseases such as: Cushing s disease Diabetes Rheumatoid arthritis Thyroid dysfunction Behavioral problems such as: Anxiety Aggression Obsessiveness Cancer and treatment side effects such as: Loss of appetite Nausea Pain Digestive issues such as: Constipation Diarrhea Irritable bowel syndrome (IBS) Muscle and skeletal issues such as: Arthritis Hip dysplasia Ligament or tendon injury Surgery recovery Neurological conditions such as: Intervertebral disc disease (IVDD) Paralysis Seizures Respiratory ailments such as: Allergies Asthma Chronic bronchitis Skin conditions such as: Allergic dermatitis Hot spots (moist dermatitis) Types of acupuncture for pets In addition to inserting needles into various points on the body, veterinary acupuncturists have a few other tools to use as Our veterinary acupuncturists may add a tiny electrical current to the dry needles (electroacupuncture) or inject vitamins or herbal medications into acupuncture points (aquapuncture). What to expect during treatment Our veterinary acupuncturists come to your home, where your pet is most Your dog or cat relaxes in their favorite spot while the veterinarian inserts acupuncture How long do acupuncture needles stay in dogs and cats? This depends on the age and condition of the pet but ranges from 5 to minutes depending on the acupuncture Is acupuncture painful for animals? Similar to acupuncture in people, pets may feel a tiny prick or nothing at all when the needles go The needles are incredibly fine and veterinary acupuncturists quickly tap them But pets that are in a lot of pain may be more guarded about certain areas of their Are cats and dogs sedated for acupuncture? Veterinarians don’t use sedation for cat or dog acupuncture because it could negate the effects of However, it is necessary for pets to be relatively still for the duration of the Our veterinary acupuncturists use positive reinforcement (treats and praise) to encourage pets to lie Most pets that we treat have no problem remaining calm and relaxed, especially since they re at Are there acupuncture side effects in dogs and cats? There are no known adverse effects for They will usually be sleepy tired the day of Typically they are back to normal the day after How often should cats and dogs get acupuncture? The optimal number of acupuncture sessions for cats and dogs It depends on your pet’s Our veterinary acupuncturists create individual treatment plans for pets on the first visit and then continue to reevaluate that plan throughout the course of Typically, we start with three acupuncture sessions in the first three After that, your veterinary acupuncturist will determine the best treatment frequency based on your pet’s progress and What does acupuncture for pets cost? Please enter your zip code on our homepage and see if we offer acupuncture in your Our prices will be Schedule a Pet Acupuncture Appointment Want to know if acupuncture could help your cat or dog?
